<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="408" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="15.[165,1373,730,1434]" pageId="15" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[167,519,1243,1276]" pageId="15" pageNumber="408">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. Salvin’s Shrew seems to have a relatively fragmented highland distribution that might be threatened by deforestation in the long run. Not much is known about Salvin’s Shrew, and additional research is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
